subject: 64 bit build support
commitMessage:
64 bit build support

Tizen toolchain team in Samsung company is planning to build Tizen
for new arm 64 bit architecture - Aarch64. But package "libscl-ui"
cannot be built for this architecture because of build errors.

The main problem is pointer size change, so fix is just cutting lowest 32 bytes
on 64-bit platforms to use them as id for timer.

Change-Id: I8f75a659ac1eb34da2c50e42c6c7f34595366a15
Signed-off-by: Vyacheslav Barinov <v.barinov@samsung.com>

comments.message:
Patch Set 1: Verified-1 Code-Review-2

no. the original code in 32bit would have guaranteed that the sendData is unique - if it's a pointer but by just using the lower 32bits means you will no longer guarantee uniqueness.

unless the void *data passed in is in fact a 32bit int value stuffed into a pointer for convenience - can you show that? (and if it is so, then there also is no point masking the lower 32bits - just cast).

Patch Set 2: Verified+1

This changes does not break armv7l and i586 build and enables aarch64 build. Build results: original: https://build.tizen.org/package/show?package=libscl-ui-fail&project=devel%3Aarm_toolchain%3AMobile%3Atest  patched: https://build.tizen.org/package/show?package=libscl-ui&project=devel%3Aarm_toolchain%3AMobile%3Atest

Patch Set 2: Verified-1

same story. it didn't change. can you guarantee that that point ONLY contains data in its lower 32bits? show to me it does, because otherwise this breaks as you lose data in the upper bits.

Patch Set 2:

Okay. The only place where the timer_event function is called from is scl/gwes/efl/sclevents-efl.cpp:614
In this function 32bit int is constructed from two 16bit ones and passed into timer_event. So there can't be any data in upper bytes.

The same situation with gtk version in sclevents-gtk.cpp:401

And this function is not exported anywhere, so it can't be called from another place with 64bit argument.

Patch Set 2: -Verified Code-Review+2

ok then. good info. just what i wanted to hear! :)
Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.
